Sonoj Convention has the permission to reproduce a video recording of my
workshop under the terms of the CC-BY 4.0 — doc/CC-BY_4.0.txt — or later,
notwithstanding others’ rights to individual exhibits.

Individual examples are published under their own licence terms,
which are listed below:

• Intro: La Réjoussance, arr. by tlw (MuseScore.com user) under CC-BY

• MIDI import: Ode to Joy, Public Domain

• Frère Jacques: PD, trivial example made for this workshop

• Die Himmel erzählen: notation and excerpt, Ⓕ The MirOS Licence

The fonts used for the slides are all covered by licences with font
embedding exceptions:

• Gentium, Gentium Italic, Inconsolatazi4varl_qu Regular (SIL OFLv1.1)
  from http://www.mirbsd.org/music/free/resources/

• NotoSansSymbols Regular, UnifrakturMaguntia (SIL OFLv1.1) a.a.O.
  for example scores

• Bravura, BravuraText, Gootville, GootvilleText, MScoreBC,
  MScoreTabulature, MScoreText, MuseJazz Book and Medium (SIL OFLv1.1),
  MScore (GPL with font embedding exception), FreeSans, FreeSerif
  optionally bold and/or italic (GPLv3 with font embedding exception)
  from MuseScore (embedded), for example scores and screenshots

• Fira Sans (SIL OFLv1.1) may occur as screenshot UI font

The images (except for the Shilouette Dæmon) are covered by the
MuseScore licence unless listed below:

• Cats at the piano: Public Domain

• NEW!: from CC0 source

• “mirabilos”: from Gentium, font embedded, Ⓕ The MirOS Licence
  (‘m’ design by smultron)

The subdirectory html/ contains a browsable export of the slides
from the MagicPoint format sources, embedding the aforementioned
fonts and the source images.

The Tₑχ/LᴬTᴇΧ-generated PDF document is also set in a Gentium body
with Fira Sans highlights. It uses styles and classes, other than
those in texlive-full stock, by Thorsten Glaser and Dominik George,
Teckids e.V. and/or tarent solutions GmbH, David Carlisle aiding.
